President Barack Obama and First Lady Michelle Obama expressed their sadness over the passing of Neil Armstrong. They described Armstrong as one of the greatest American heroes of all time. They highlighted his historic achievement of being the first person to set foot on the moon during the Apollo 11 mission in 1969, which showcased the American spirit and the belief that anything is possible with determination and innovation. The Obamas also noted that Armstrong's legacy lives on through those who continue to explore the unknown and push the boundaries of space exploration. They emphasized the significant impact of Armstrong's "one small step" in human achievement.